SYNOPSIS
========
   #include <files.h>
   int file_size(stringÂ file)

DESCRIPTION
===========
   Return: 
      - `FSIZE_NOFILE` (-1) : indicates that the file either does not 
        exist, or that it is not readable for the calling object/user.
      - `FSIZE_DIR` (-2) : indicates that it is a directory.

   Returns the size of the file in bytes.

SEE ALSO
========
   write_file(E), write_bytes(E), read_file(E), read_bytes(E), get_dir(E)
